## Environment Variables

All variables are **required** unless a default is shown.

| Variable | Required | Description | Example |
|----------|----------|-------------|---------|
| `AOS_E2E_BASE_URL` | Yes | Root URL of the application under test | `http://localhost:4000` |
| `AOS_E2E_USER` | Yes | Login username / email | `tester@example.com` |
| `AOS_E2E_PASS` | Yes | Login password | *(use `.env` or shell secret)* |
| `AOS_E2E_STORAGE_STATE_PATH` | No | Override storage state path | `.auth/storage_state.json` |

Set variables in your shell or a local `.env` file (never commit credentials):

```bash
export AOS_E2E_BASE_URL="http://localhost:4000"
export AOS_E2E_USER="your-test-user"
export AOS_E2E_PASS="your-test-password"
```

